description:
This legendary recording from the 1950's has been featured in several films and still stands as one of the great recordings of all time.  It is a version of the Latin Mass based on traditional Congolese songs, arranged by Father Guido Haazen, a Franciscan Friar from Belgium, and originally performed and recorded in 1958 by &quot;Les Troubadours du Roi Baudouin&quot;, a choir of Congolese children from Kamina. The recording includes the mass as well as traditional songs.


More - http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Missa_Luba

